            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>a = b</m>;
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>a > b</m>.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        Is the following proposition concerning sets true or false?
        Either provide a proof that it is true or a counterexample showing it is false.
        If <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> are subsets of some universal set,
        then exactly one of the following is true:
        <ul>
